===Usage===
:{{Tlx|{{PAGENAME}}|&lt;guideline category&gt;|&lt;category sort key&gt;|&lt;shortcut&gt;|&lt;shortcut&gt;|...}}

=== New guidelines require approval ===
If you're writing a new guideline, or substantially revising one, please remember to give the community significant time to consider your proposal.  See [[WP:PROPOSAL]] for the current best practice on advertising proposals.

For a short introduction on how to go from a ''proposal'' to a Wikipedia ''style guideline'', see: [[:Category:Wikipedia proposals]] and [[WP:How to contribute to Wikipedia guidance|How to contribute to Wikipedia guidance]].

===Parameters===
:#&lt;guideline category&gt;: one of the following should be used:
:#:* <tt>behavioral guideline</tt>
:#:* <tt>content guideline</tt>
:#:* <tt>deletion guideline</tt>
:#:* <tt>editing guideline</tt>
:#:* <tt>naming convention</tt>
:#:* <tt>notability guideline</tt>
:#:* <tt>style guideline</tt>
:#&lt;category sort key&gt;: for e.g. ''notability'' or ''naming conventions'' guidelines, sort by what is in the parentical disambiguator, examples:
:#*[[wikipedia:notability (websites)]]: &lt;category sort key&gt; = '''Websites'''
:#*[[wikipedia:naming conventions (people)]]: &lt;category sort key&gt; = '''People'''
:#&lt;shortcut&gt;: optional, [[Wikipedia:Shortcut|shortcut]] like for instance '''WP:SHORT'''
:#&lt;shortcut&gt;: Optional second shortcut. Five shortcuts can be passed in total, each as a separate parameter.


